{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Encapsulation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Each layer (except the physical layer) adds its own header. This is called encapsulating the packet.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In a router in the middle, the link header will be removed and replaced with a new one. This is needed because each link is different.\par}
